defs.name: DEFAULT_MIN_CAP
defs.docs: Minimum buffer capacity for a deque.

defs.name: FLUSH_THRESHOLD_BYTES
defs.docs:
If a buffer of at least this size is retired, thread-local garbage is flushed so that it gets
 deallocated as soon as possible.

defs.name: Empty
defs.docs: The deque was empty at the time of stealing.

defs.name: Data
defs.docs: Some data has been successfully stolen.

defs.name: Retry
defs.docs: Lost the race for stealing data to another concurrent operation. Try again.

defs.name: Steal
defs.docs: Possible outcomes of a steal operation.

defs.name: Buffer
defs.docs: A buffer that holds elements in a deque.

defs.name: cap
defs.docs: Capacity of the buffer. Always a power of two.

defs.name: Inner
defs.docs: Internal data that is shared between the deque and its stealers.

defs.name: min_cap
defs.docs: Minimum capacity of the buffer. Always a power of two.

defs.name: Stealer
defs.docs: A stealer that steals elements from the top of a deque.
